      "end": 4.88,
      "text": "This is a LibriVox recording. All LibriVox recordings are in the public domain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 5.7,
      "end": 11.46,
      "text": "For more information and to find out how you can volunteer, please visit LibriVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 12.72,
      "end": 15.88,
      "text": "ASOP's fables, the dog, the cock, and the fox.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 16.86,
      "end": 20.42,
      "text": "A dog and a cock became great friends and agreed to travel together.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 21.24,
      "end": 24.84,
      "text": "At nightfall, the cock flew up into the branches of a tree to roost,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 25.08,
      "end": 28.04,
      "text": "while the dog grilled himself up inside the trunk, which was hollow.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 28.04,
      "end": 32.08,
      "text": "At break of day, the cock woke up and crew, as usual.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 32.88,
      "end": 38.08,
      "text": "A fox heard and wishing to make breakfast of him, came and stood under the tree and begged him to come down.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 38.64,
      "end": 43.96,
      "text": "I should so like, said he, to make the acquaintance of one who has such a beautiful voice.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 44.76,
      "end": 49.1,
      "text": "The cock replied, would you just wake by Porter who sleeps at the foot of the tree?",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 49.66,
      "end": 51.16,
      "text": "He'll open the door and let you in.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 52.0,
      "end": 57.34,
      "text": "The fox accordingly wrapped on the trunk, when out rushed the dog, and tore him into pieces.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 59.04,
      "end": 62.94,
      "text": "End of ASOP, the dog, the cock, and the fox.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
